Design a complete mobile app UI for PhaseFlow — a cycle-synced fitness app powered by Gemma 4 AI. The app recommends workouts based on the user's menstrual cycle phase and energy levels.

═══════════════════════════════════════════
INCLUSIVITY PRINCIPLES — NON-NEGOTIABLE
═══════════════════════════════════════════

This app is for ALL menstruators — regardless of gender identity. This must be reflected in every design decision:

• Language: Never use "women", "female", or "she/her". Use "menstruators", "people who cycle", "you", "your body". Phase names are clinical and neutral: Menstrual, Follicular, Ovulatory, Luteal.
• Visuals: No gender-coded imagery (no pink bows, no female silhouettes, no Mars/Venus symbols). Use abstract body illustrations, geometric shapes, and fluid forms that represent all body types.
• Color: Do NOT use pink as the primary brand color. Choose a palette that is grounded, natural, and warm without being coded as feminine. Suggested direction: deep sage green + warm terracotta + soft off-white + deep charcoal. Or propose your own — just avoid pastels and stereotypically feminine palettes.
• Body illustrations: If used, show a range of body types, skin tones, and presentations. Keep illustrations minimal and abstract — no gendered clothing or hairstyles.
• Tone: Clinical where accurate (phase names), warm where emotional (energy check-in). Never cutesy or overly delicate.
• Icon set: Use neutral geometric icons. No gender symbols, no lipstick, no flowers as primary UI elements.

═══════════════════════════════════════════
BRAND & VISUAL IDENTITY
═══════════════════════════════════════════

App name: PhaseFlow
Team: Infradian Labs
Tagline: "Train with your cycle, not against it."

Color palette (use this exactly or propose a strong alternative):
• Primary: Deep sage #4A7C59 (grounded, natural, not "feminine green")
• Accent: Warm terracotta #C0622B (energy, warmth, strength)
• Background: Off-white #F7F5F1 (warm neutral, not clinical white)
• Surface: #FFFFFF
• Text primary: #1C1C1E
• Text secondary: #6B6B6B
• Phase colors (use sparingly, for phase cards only):
  – Menstrual: #B84C3A (warm red, not hot pink)
  – Follicular: #4A7C59 (sage — same as primary)
  – Ovulatory: #5C4B8A (deep violet — not purple-pink)
  – Luteal: #A0722A (warm amber)

Typography:
• Heading: DM Sans Bold or Plus Jakarta Sans — modern, neutral, no serifs
• Body: Inter Regular
• Numeric/data: JetBrains Mono or IBM Plex Mono for cycle day numbers and stats

Aesthetic direction: Clean, minimal, clinical-warm. Think: the aesthetic of a high-quality health journal meets a modern fitness tracker. No gradients. No decorative flourishes. Strong white space. Data-forward but warm.

═══════════════════════════════════════════
SCREENS TO DESIGN — ALL ON MOBILE (390×844px)
═══════════════════════════════════════════

Design all screens for iPhone 14 Pro (390×844). Show them arranged in a flow on the canvas with arrows connecting the user journey.

---

SCREEN 1: ONBOARDING — Welcome
• Full-screen illustration: abstract fluid shapes representing a cycle (circular, rhythmic, neutral)
• Text: "Train with your cycle, not against it."
• Subtext: "Personalised workouts for every phase of your menstrual cycle."
• CTA button: "Get started"
• Small text below: "For all menstruators, regardless of gender identity."
• NO gender imagery. NO pink.

SCREEN 2: ONBOARDING — Data source selection
• Title: "How would you like to sync your cycle?"
• Four options as selectable cards with icons:
  – Enter manually (pencil icon)
  – Apple Health (health heart icon — neutral)
  – Google Fit (activity icon)
  – Flo app (leaf/flow icon — NOT a flower, NOT pink)
• Each card: icon + label + one-line description
• "Flo app" selected state shown (active border + checkmark)
• Small note: "Flo connects via secure OAuth. No password stored."
• CTA: "Continue"

SCREEN 3: ONBOARDING — Cycle dates
• Title: "When did your last cycle begin?"
• Large date picker input: DD / MM / YYYY
• Cycle length input: "My cycle is typically __ days" (slider 21–35 days, default 28)
• Informational note: "Not sure? Enter your best estimate — PhaseFlow learns over time."
• CTA: "Continue"

SCREEN 4: ONBOARDING — Goals
• Title: "What do you want from PhaseFlow?"
• Multi-select chip grid (toggle on/off):
  Build strength · Manage energy · Improve endurance · Reduce cycle symptoms · Stress relief · Flexibility · Weight management
• CTA: "Let's go"

SCREEN 5: HOME — Dashboard
• Status bar at top
• Greeting: "Day 22 · Luteal phase" in large type, phase color accent
• Phase card (full width, subtle phase-colored background):
  – Phase name + day number
  – One-line description: "Progesterone is peaking. Energy may taper — listen to your body."
  – Horizontal cycle progress bar showing day 22 of 28
  – Energy level dots (3/5 filled = expected energy)
• Energy check-in row: "How do you feel today?" — five buttons: Drained / Low / Okay / Good / Strong (NOT "Great" — avoid gendered enthusiasm)
• Section: "Today's workout" — workout recommendation card (see Screen 6 detail)
• Section: "Phase tip" — short text card with a recovery or nutrition note
• "Log yesterday's session →" link
• Bottom navigation: Home / Calendar / Log / Settings (neutral icons)

SCREEN 6: WORKOUT RECOMMENDATION CARD (embedded in Home, also full screen view)
• Workout name: "Flow Pilates + Core" in large heading
• Tags: "35 min" · "Low intensity" · "Luteal phase"
• "Why this workout" section (subtle background, Gemma AI badge):
  – Two sentences explaining the phase-appropriate logic
  – Small badge: "Recommended by Gemma 4"
• Exercise list: 4 items with phase-color bullet dots
• Warm-up note (one line)
• "Start workout" button (primary CTA, full width, phase color)
• "Refresh suggestion" ghost button below

SCREEN 7: WORKOUT LOG — Input state
• Back navigation: "← Log"
• Title: "How did it go?"
• Subtitle: "Write naturally — our AI will extract the details."
• Text field: large, multiline, placeholder: "e.g. Felt stronger than expected today, finished all sets..."
• Workout name input above (smaller)
• "Analyse with Gemma 4" CTA button (Gemma violet accent)
• Horizontal scrollable chips showing example phrases

SCREEN 8: WORKOUT LOG — Parsed result state
• Same layout as Screen 7 but text field is now locked/grey
• Parsed result card appearing below the text:
  – "Gemma read this as:" header
  – Three data rows: Energy (2/5) · Completion (55%) · Mood (tired)
  – "What PhaseFlow will adjust" box with Gemma's one-sentence adaptation note
• "Save log" primary button
• "Edit note" ghost link
• Gemma badge: "Analysed on-device · Private"

SCREEN 9: CYCLE CALENDAR VIEW
• Month view calendar
• Each day circle colored by phase: phase-appropriate subtle fill
• Today highlighted with ring
• Logged workout days shown with small dot below date
• Phase legend at bottom: Menstrual · Follicular · Ovulatory · Luteal
• Upcoming phase preview card below calendar: "Follicular phase starts in 6 days — your high-energy window."

SCREEN 10: SETTINGS — Data & Privacy
• Section: "Cycle data source"
  – Connected: Flo app (green connected badge) with "Disconnect" option
  – Other sources: Apple Health (off), Google Fit (off), Manual (off)
• Section: "AI & Privacy"
  – Toggle: "Run Gemma on-device (recommended)" — ON, with note: "Your data never leaves your phone"
  – Toggle: "Cross-device sync (Supabase)" — OFF
• Section: "About"
  – App version, GitHub link, Infradian Labs credit

